                </fig>
                <p>The result of LFIA was recorded within 6 hours, and the diagnostic time from the moment of the clinical material inoculation to obtaining the result of the toxigenic corynebacteria presence/absence was 24&#x2013;30 hours. Thus, using the LFIA-based approach, the clinical diagnosis of diphtheria can be confirmed or questioned by the end of the second working day from the start of the bacteriological study.</p>
            </sec>
